(1166, 'Project 3: Inserting Video into Your Web Design', 'As you can see from this project, the code needed to add video to your web page is not very complicated. The hardest part is the actual creation of the video in the first place. This is the objective of HTML5 video support. You should not be distracted by the complexities of inserting video into a web page; your focus should be on the creation of the content.\r\nAs with video, audio is now becoming much easier to work with. Also, as with video, the challenge you have is the two different audio CODECs being supported by the different browsers: &shy;Ogg and MPEG4. The good news is that you can use the new source attribute with your VIDEO or AUDIO element to &shy;target different file types supported by Mozilla&rsquo;s FireFox, Google&rsquo;s Chrome, Apple&rsquo;s Safari, or Microsoft&rsquo;s Internet Explorer 9.\r\nRich media is prevalent on the Web. Adding it to your web site is now as easy as inserting an image.', 0, 0, '', 275, 163, 174, 'david:html5-project3.pdf', 0, '2012-11-19 09:11:55', NULL),
(1167, 'Erfahrungen mit HTML5-Video', 'export-frames gibt je nach Video-Format (ogv, mp4, webm) verschiedene Frames. Das ist etwas &auml;rgerlich. Am besten passt webm, gibt allerdings bei Browsern mit mp4-Wiedergabe eine minime Verz&ouml;gerung.', 11, 26, '', 0, 0, 0, '', 0, '2012-12-04 08:46:27', NULL),
